local_customer_id,sumsub_external_user_id
# Sumsub Test ID Mappings
# ========================
# This file maps local customer IDs to known Sumsub external user IDs.
# 
# Setup:
#   1. Copy this file to sumsub_external_user_ids.csv (same directory)
#   2. Add your Sumsub external user IDs
#   3. Restart containers: make restart
#   4. Run: SUMSUB_USE_TEST_IDS=true make materialize-sumsub
#
# Format:
#   - If local_customer_id is provided: explicit mapping (that ID -> this Sumsub ID)
#   - If local_customer_id is empty: ID is added to random pool (any customer can use it)
#
# Examples:
#
# Explicit mapping - this local customer always uses this Sumsub ID:
# 019c67f7-d360-77c3-adf8-0aa447591778,sumsub-external-id-123
#
# Random pool - any customer without explicit mapping picks randomly from these:
# ,sumsub-external-id-456
# ,sumsub-external-id-789
